{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Remediated blocker f5c3df0429fdffa41 by preserving required original_index labels through verifier tuple splitting and index-keyed reassembly. For blocker f09050c2dfd6b2fbc, clarified that the singleton phase is non-releasable test scaffolding with no production consumer or independently closable outcome; splitting it would create an orphan contract/prompt task, so the approved leaf remains one atomic delivery with a fail-fast internal checkpoint. Also applied advisory feedback feb2d8720f9f4746d and fc03e74e5936078ea by restoring the epic-required single Pass-3 pipeline and specifying every decide/coach YAML data-flow edge. Realigned ff78c97ce9c3a3a0d to the certified epic: any prerequisite indeterminacy yields unsigned INDETERMINATE while DET blockers remain visible in the blocking array. Added exact model, prompt-front-matter, tail-conflict, seam, identity, and empty-indeterminate tests. Runtime rollback flag advice is declined: this story writes no migration/state and has a safe code-revert path; a flag would add an unapproved behavior gap."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784574241693420001,"uuid":"a613bda6-3c96-4fe4-be5f-7ca97b78fb40"}